main event: One unidentified object was observed in Rochester, New York on March 12, 1965, for approximately 10 seconds.
interesting points: The object was reported as 'round or saucer-like in appearance',The object appeared to be 2-3 feet in diameter,Two F-101 jet interceptors were launched to investigate but the object had vanished by the time they arrived,The observation was made at a recording station,There were multiple witnesses to the sighting.
